The paper deals with the integration of aerial and ground images for surface reconstruction in urban environments, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed approach also involves photogrammetry and multi-view stereo, which are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents experimental evaluations and comparisons, which suggests a potential application of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
